captions.text:
Burmese Pythons are an invasive species from South East Asia, 
 that have found a home in the Florida's Everglades.
These large constrictors compete with American Alligators as top predators.

For the first time in history, these two 
 top predators battling for the same resources.
Larger Alligators with their powerful jaws have a distinct advantage over the pythons.

The Alligator holds on to the python with 
 power exceeding 2000 pounds per square inch.
It is next to impossible for the python to escape this hold.
Nevertheless, the alligator gives way to the python.
After an exhausting battle that last for hours, an unusual twist of fate occurs.

On rare occasions the burmese python is able 
 to intimidate the alligator into a retreat.

title: Python vs Alligator  01 -- Real Fight -- Python attacks Alligator
